uwsgi (2.0.15-5) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Simplify packaging by offloading some parts to separate source:
    + Stop build plugins for MongoDB/GridFS V8.
    + Drop binary packages uwsgi-mongodb-plugins uwsgi-plugin-v8.
    + Stop build-depend on libv8-dev libmongoclient-dev
      libboost-thread-dev libboost-filesystem-dev
  * Update package relations:
    + Fix have uwsgi-dev recommend git cppcheck.
    + Have uwsgi-core provide virtual abi package.
    + Fix have uwsgi-dev depend on uwsgi-core python.
    + Fix explicitly build-depend on zlib1g-dev.
    + Fix have uwsgi-dev depend on zlib1g-dev.
  * Include debhelper snippet and sequence with uwsgi-dev.
    Have uwsgi-dev enhance debhelper.
  * Use section httpd (not web) for most binary packages.

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Thu, 28 Sep 2017 14:55:49 +0200

uwsgi (2.0.15-4) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Extend long description of uwsgi-dev package to please ftpmasters.

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Thu, 31 Aug 2017 10:39:17 +0200

uwsgi (2.0.15-3) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Introduce package uwsgi-dev for building external modules.
  * Declare compliance with Debian Policy 4.1.0.
  * Update copyright info: Use https protocol in file format URL.
  * Modernize cdbs:
    + Drop upstream-tarball hints: Use gbp import-orig --uscan.
    + Do copyright-check in maintainer script (not during build).
      Relax build-dependency on cdbs.
      Stop build-depend on licensecheck libregexp-assemble-perl
      libimage-exiftool-perl libfont-ttf-perl.
  * Tighten lintian overrides regarding License-Reference.
  * Modernize maintainer script pkgarchs.sh.
  * Advertise DEP-3 format in patch headers.

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Wed, 30 Aug 2017 10:39:33 +0200

