 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Mon, 12 Oct 2015 20:04:04 +0200

uwsgi (2.0.11.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ upstream ]
  * New release(s).
    Bugfixes:
    + Fix pypy misuse of ffi.string.
    + Fix detection for gcc 5.
    + Fix shared sockets for gateways.
    + Change psgi abs to labs: offset is declared as a long.
    + Add null terminator to uwsgi_get_dot_h() and uwsgi_config_py().
    + Fix thread waiting during stop/restart.
    + Fix chain reloading verbosity.
    + Fix python spooler job reference counting.
    + Various static analysis improvements.
    + Fix sharedarea support for very big ranges.
    + Fix gzip transformation for zero-sized responses.
    + Fix management of https client certificate authentication.
    + Fix OpenBSD build.
    + Fix TMPFILE permissions.
    + Fix HTTPS router resource deallocation and file descriptors leak.
    + Suppress ssl errors when errno is 0.

    New Features and improvements:
    + Evil memory monitors (like --evil-reload-on-rss) are now
      asynchronously managed by a dedicated thread.
    + New routing action fixpathinfo
    + New routing vars uwsgi[sor] and time[micros].
    + New function wait-for-socket.
    + wait-for-* can now be used as a hook.
    + New hook unix_signal.

  [ Jonas Smedegaard ]
  * Add TODO on auto-enabling core apache proxy module.
  * Fix use only first Ruby kind listed by dh_ruby.
    Closes: bug#788957, #791847. Thanks to Andreas Beckmann, Christian
    Hofstaedtler and Antonio Terceiro.
  * Revert git packaging branch to master.
  * Update package relations:
    + Build-depend on libacl1-dev: Needed by glusterfs-common.
    + Build-depend on libsystemd-dev (with libsystemd-journal-dev only
      as fallback).
  * Update copyright info:
    + List main license as plain GPL-2: (no newer and without linking
      exception): Relaxations are uncertain where they apply if at all.
    + Adjust questionably licensed files to match general license, and
      add comments.
    + Use License-Grant and License-Reference fields.
      Thanks to Ben Finney.
    + Extend Files section for GPL-2+ licensed files.
  * Add lintian overrides regarding license in License-Reference field.
    See bug#786450.
  * Remove debian/source/local-options: abort-on-upstream-changes and
    unapply-patches are default in dpkg-source since 1.16.1.
  * Stop build coroae: libcoro-perl is broken (See bug#787500).
  * Limit uwsgi to logrotate only below apps: clash with uwsgi-emperor.
  * Modernize git-buildpackage config: Drop "git-" prefix.
  * Bump debhelper compatibility level to 9.
  * Add lintian override regarding debhelper 9.
  * Update supported archs:
    + Drop sparc.
    + Add mips64el (except for luajit or rados).
    + Add hurd-i386 for luajit.
  * Fix declare uwsgi-proxy module-dependency on core proxy module.
    Closes: Bug#785610. Thanks to Joseph Graham.
  * Fix pass die-on-term to emperor init script.
    Closes: Bug#799971. Thanks to PF4Public.

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Tue, 06 Oct 2015 15:18:21 +0200

uwsgi (2.0.10-2) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Add patch 2005 to fix compilation of mono plugin for GNU/kFreeBSD.
  * Disable tuntap plugin on GNU/Hurd.

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Wed, 18 Mar 2015 18:44:28 +0100

uwsgi (2.0.10-1) experimental; urgency=medium

  [ upstream ]
  * New release.
    Bugfixes:
    + Don’t lower security standards with gcc 4.9 (Riccardo Magliocchetti)
    + Ensure Perl/PSGI gets passed least two params to xs_input_seek.
    + Fix Perl/PSGI multiple interpreters usage.
    + Fix spooler scandir usage.
    + Fix exception handler arguments management.
    + Fix ‘log-master’ + ‘daemonize2’ disables all logging.
    + Fix http Range header management.
    New Features and improvements:
    + Add safeexec hook.
    + Add emperor-wrapper-fallback and –emperor-wrapper-override
      options.
    + Add support for UNIX sockets to rsyslog.
    + Add forcecl transformation.

  [ Jonas Smedegaard ]
  * Drop patch cherry-picked upstream now merged.
  * Update copyright info:
    + Extend coverage for main upstream author to include recent years.
    + Add myself as copyright holder.
  * Move packaging to team-maintenance: Set team list as maintainer, and
    demote Janos to uploader.
  * Declare compile flags explicitly in rules (not via environment).
  * Fix limit gccgo plugin to supported archs.

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Wed, 18 Mar 2015 14:39:40 +0100

uwsgi (2.0.9-1) experimental; urgency=medium

  [ upstream ]
  * New release 2.0.7.
    Bugfixes:
    + Fix mod_proxy_uwsgi for non-blocking mode.
    + Fix master-fifo + cheaper.
    + Fix leak on error in bind_to_unix.
    + atexit hooks works in cheaped workers too.
    + atexit hooks works in gevent mode too during shutdown.
    + Fix carbon command line option value after reload.
    + Do not honour Emperor throttling on the first run.
    + Fix Mono plugin.
    + Fix peer name in corerouters.
    + Fix stop signal for daemons.
    + Varios ssl/tls fixes in https/spdy router.
    + Fix python3 –py-auto-reload-ignore.
    + Fix modifiers in corerouters.
    + Support for yajl from homebrew.
    + Ensure that we call any DESTROY hooks on psgix.harakiri.commit.
    + Fix systemdlogger compilation with -Werror=format-security.
    + Fix unmasked websockets.
    + Fix perl latent refcounting bug.
    New Features and improvements:
    + Improved PyPy support for Linux.
    + Fastrouter now supports post-buffering.
    + Have psgi/perl plugin expose the uwsgi::opt hash.
    + New pull-header option.
    + New active-workers signal target.
    + New httpdumb routing action.

  [ Jonas Smedegaard ]
  * Fix have uwsgi-plugin-python3 provide httpd-wsgi3 (not httpd-wsgi).
    Closes: bug#769053. Thanks to Brian May.
  * Fix build-depend explicitly on libpcre3-dev.
    Closes: bug#771840. Thanks to Logan Rosen.
  * Update patches:
    + Drop patch cherry-picked upstream now merged.
    + Unfuzz patch 1002.
    + Add patch 1009 to fix java paths.
      Closes: bug#774026, #774027. Thanks to Jakub Wilk.

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Wed, 11 Mar 2015 14:59:39 +0100

uwsgi (2.0.8-1~exp2) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Replace patch 1005 with improved upstream fixes. Closes: bug#754854.
  * Modernize uWSGI Emperor sysV init script:
    + Rewrite to use init-d-script.
    + Replace ENABLED variable in default file with comment instructing
      to use update-rc.d.
    + Have uwsgi-emperor depend on recent sysvinit-utils (not lsb-base
      or recent initscripts).

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Thu, 06 Nov 2014 23:33:42 +0100

uwsgi (2.0.8-1~exp1) experimental; urgency=medium

  [ upstream ]
  * New release 2.0.7.
    Bugfixes:
    + Fix PHP SCRIPT_NAME usage when --php-app is in place.
    + Allow "appendn" hook without second argument.
    + Fix heap corruption in the Carbon plugin.
    + Fix getifaddrs() memory management.
    + Fix tcsetattr() usage.
    + Fix kevent usage of return value.
    + Ensure PSGI response headers are in the right format.
    + Fix reloading of attached daemons.
    + Fix SSL/TLS shutdown.
    + Fix mountpoint logic for paths not ending with "/".
    + Fix Python3 support in spooler decorators.
    New Features and improvements:
    + RTSP and chunked input (backported from 2.1) for the HTTP router.
    + Custom hook --hook-post-fork to call actions after each fork().
    + Support building asyncio plugin for Python 2, using trollius.
    + Add sweep_on_full, clear_on_full and no_expire to --cache2.
    + Susped options wait-for-fs/mountpoints (backported from 2.1).
    + Improved offload API.
    + Allows building plugins from remote sources as embedded.
    + Automatically manage HTTP_X_FORWARDED_PROTO.

  [ Jonas Smedegaard ]
  * Enable core plugins logcrypto logpipe msgpack pty router_expires
    router_hash router_metrics router_radius router_redis router_xmldir
    stats_pusher_file stats_pusher_socket transformation_chunked
    transformation_offload transformation_template webdav xattr zabbix.
  * Enable core plugins logzmq mongrel2 forkptyrouter (except on the
    Hurd).
  * Enable core plugin tuntap (except on kFreeBSD).
  * Enable core plugin systemd_logger (only on linux archs).
  * Enable plugins separately packaged:
    + gevent
    + asyncio
    + tornado
    + Closure/ring
    + Servlet 2.5
    + MongoDB and GridFS plugins (on supported archs)
    + GlusterFS (on supported archs)
    + Mono/ASP.NET (on supported archs)
    + GNU Go (on supported archs)
  * Update package relations:
    + Build-depend on mongodb-dev, libboost-thread-dev and
      libboost-filesystem-dev: Needed for MongoDB.
    + Build-depend on glusterfs-common: Needed for GlusterFS.
    + Build-depend on mono-devel and cli-common-dev: Needed for mono.
    + Build-depend on gccgo: Needed for GNU Go.
    + Build-depend on libsystemd-journal-dev: Needed for systemd_logger.
    + Build-depend on python-trollius: Needed for asyncio on Python 2.
  * Adjust git-buildpackage config for experimental branch.
  * Add patch 1008 to unconditionally use sys/xattr.h (not attr/xattr.h
    on Linux), avoiding webdav plugin linkage against libattr and
    hopefully fixing FTBFS for pty plugin on KFreeBSD.
  * Fix typo in patch 1007: Caused FTBFS with pty plugin enabled.
  * Improve package dependency auto-resolving:
    + Normalize suite (i.e. suffix like -security).
    + Swap "all" with "any", to fit use in control file.

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Wed, 05 Nov 2014 21:34:16 +0100

uwsgi (2.0.7-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ upstream ]
  * New release 2.0.7.
    Bugfixes:
    + Fix counters in statsd plugin.
    + Fix caching in php plugin.
    + Fix management of system users starting with a number.
    + Fix request body readline using memmove instead of memcpy.
    + Ignore "user" namespace in setns (still a source of problems).
    + Fix Python3 rpc bytes/string mess (result: we support both).
    + Do not destroy the Emperor on failed mount hooks.
    + Fix symbol lookup error in the Mono plugin on OS X.
    + Fix fastcgi and scgi protocols error when out of buffer happens.
    + Fix solaris/smartos I/O management.
    + Fix 2 memory leaks in the rpc subsystem.
    + Fix rados plugin PUT method.
    + Fix multiple python mountpoints with multiple threads in cow mode.
    + stats UNIX socket is now deleted by vacuum.
    + Fix off-by-one corruption in cache LRU mode.
    + Force single-cpu build in cygwin.
    New Features and improvements:
    + Allow calling the spooler from every cpython context.
    + Add store_delete flag to cache2 option.
    + Extend file logger to allow rotation.
    + vassals plugin extended with hooks vassal and vassal_before_exec.
    + broodlord subsystem improved with option –vassal-sos.

  [ Jonas Smedegaard ]
  * Fix auto-resolve as "none" (not empty string) when no archs found.
  * Add patch 1007 to fix support pty on GNU/Hurd.
  * Stop repackage source: Upstream no longer ship binary java class
    file.
  * Adjust architecture-dependent plugins:
    + Enable Ceph/RADOS for s390x and sparc.
    + Enable Greenlet for armel and ppc64el.
    + Enable OpenJDK 7 for armhf and ppc64el.
  * Drop patch 1006: Adopted upstream.
  * Update Vcs-Browser URL to use cgit web frontend.
  * Declare compliance with Debian Policy 3.9.6.

 -- Jonas Smedegaard <dr@jones.dk>  Sat, 25 Oct 2014 20:50:17 +0200

uwsgi (2.0.6~dfsg-8) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Resolve Ruby kinds in backport-friendly manner (see bug#755779).
  * Stop uwsgi-plugins-all needlessly depending directly on
    uwsgi-plugin-php: Pulled in via uwsgi-app-integration-plugins.
  * Fix enable plugin matheval (as intended since 1.9.15-1).
  * Fix mention Ruby native threads in uwsgi-plugins-all long
    description.
  * Fix exclude coroae plugin from auto-resolved plugin list in
    uwsgi-core long description.
  * Improve pkgarchs.sh script to auto-resolve archs:
    + Fix support experimental suite.
    + Fix strip duplicates.
    + Fix mention all its dependencies in header.
    + Fix strip leading (not only trailing) space.
  * Fix build-depend unconditionally on ruby: Needed to resolve default
    ruby version (see bug#755779).
    Closes: bug#758270.

